The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Asansol, Sept. 7: A woman was crushed to death when a portion of her 60-year-old two-storey house near Asansol caved in amid incessant rain this morning.    
	Monika Mondal, 40, lived in Kulti with her husband Nikhil, and son Sabyasachi. None of them was at home during the mishap. Nikhil was at his medical store and Sabyasachi at school. Monikas eyes, however, will bring light to someone. She had pledged them to an eye institute.         
	Durgapur: Thick smoke billowed from cracks on the ground in the Ratibati coal mine area of Ranigunj, triggering panic among villagers. Eastern Coalfields officials who visited the area, 230km from Calcutta, said illegal miners had dug deep and the coal had caught fire.         
	Behrampore: A man was killed by his brother-in-law in Nadia alle- gedly because he could not pay for the upbringing of his children. They lived with the latter.                                                                                                                                                                       
